{{technical|date=March 2013}}
In [[mathematics]], a '''monopole''' is a [[Connection (fiber bundle)|connection]] over a [[principal bundle]] ''G'' with a section of the associated [[adjoint bundle]].

==Physical interpretation==

Physically, the section can be interpreted as a ''[[Higgs field]]'', where the connection and Higgs field should{{why|date=December 2016}} satisfy the [[Bogomolny equations]] and be of [[finite action]].

